      "description": "Available is a 2008 Porsche Cayman S, a definitive mid-engine performer featuring the 3.4L M97 flat-six engine equipped with VarioCam Plus. This example utilizes a precise six-speed manual transaxle, ensuring an engaging connection to the rear-wheel-drive assembly. The chassis remains taut, benefiting from a MacPherson strut suspension configuration and staggered alloy wheels that optimize lateral grip. Braking is handled by four-piston monobloc calipers over ventilated rotors, providing consistent thermal management and pedal feel. Recent preventative maintenance includes a cooling system overhaul and a fresh rear main seal, ensuring the powertrain remains leak-free and robust. While showing light signs of road use, the mechanical geometry and drivetrain synchronization are excellent, offering a pure, analog driving experience for the discerning pilot.",
